social_posts.post_text:
I think a lot sometimes, I think we all do. I can be critical of myself. There’s always something we can look at and be unhappy with. But the goal is always to find something to be happy with. Something that fulfills us. This craft will fill up my cup every time. It’s always been there for me. This is when I’m the most articulate. This is how I feel, comprehend and explain. My experiences, my duality, my practices and emotions are in its pure and raw form. My life is my influence to everything. If we’ve shared memories, you been there for me, invested in me or even taking the time to have a conversation with me. I just want to say thank you. I’m thankful for this craft. This is when I embody who I am.

Steps by me btw

DETROIT WYA? FIRST TIME VISITING AND TEACHING IN DETROIT, PULL UP ON ME THURSDAY NIGHT. 
SEE YALL THERE.
8:45pm @release_detroit

GRAND RAPIDS, DETROIT and everywhere in between… we have BIG NEWS! We are hosting our first ever class OPEN TO THE PUBLIC! Book your calendars, move your schedules and come train with a mastermind THIS WEDNESDAY 4/19 7 - 8:30 pm. It will be advanced choreography but ALL levels are welcome! We will hold a Q&A Industry Discussion for the last 10 minutes and class will be filmed by @mattdavidcreative. Josh Cruz is from Houston, Texas and and actively working in the dance industry. This artist is incredibly knowledgeable and we can’t wait to share this opportunity with you.

Danced/Assisted Choreo Credits — Tinashe, Asher Angel, Various KPop Groups & artists such as (BTS , GOT7, NCT 127, Jung Kook etc) 

Mentors/Trained Under — Antoine Troupe, Kolanie Marks, Andye J, Alexander Chung, Alex Fetbroth, Max Pham & Andrew Baterina.

Worked under Choreographers — Dexter Carr, Sienna Lalau, Ivan Kumoev, Alexander Chung and Nicky Anderson.

Class will take place at Moveir Dance Studio
2485 Burlingame Ave SW.
Wyoming, Michigan 49509

Essence Company Members: $10
Non-Members: $15

Please reach out with any questions and share with your friends!
